MAPPING.DESCRIPTION: This mapping populates the rps.TAPC_FNC_SUMM_RBATE_AMTS summary table. Input is the VAPC_DETAIL view. The SQ uses a SQL OVERRIDE!!
MAPPING.NAME: m_Populate_RPSDM_TAPC_FNC_SUMM_RBAT_AMTS

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT VAPC_DETAIL.PERIOD_ID , VAPC_DETAIL.RBATE_ID , VAPC_DETAIL.LCM_CODE , VAPC_DETAIL.EXTNL_SRC_CODE , VAPC_DETAIL.EXTNL_LVL_ID1 , VAPC_DETAIL.NDC , SUM( VAPC_DETAIL.UNIT_QTY) , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.DAYS_SPLY) , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.INGRD_CST) , VAPC_DETAIL.CNTRL_NO , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.RBATE_ACCESS) , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.RBATE_MRKT_SHR) , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.RBATE_ADMIN_FEE) , VAPC_DETAIL.CLM_USE_SRX_CD , VAPC_DETAIL.INV_MODEL , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.AMT_PAID) , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.CNTRC_FEE_PAID) , SUM(VAPC_DETAIL.AMT_COPAY) , COALESCE(VAPC_DETAIL.RBEL_CLNT_CD,' ') , VAPC_DETAIL.MAR_CD , SUM(CASE CLAIM_TYPE WHEN '+1' THEN 1 WHEN '-1' THEN -1 ELSE 0 END) AS CLM_CNT , COALESCE(TMAIL_SPCLTY_NABP.PHMCY_DSPNS_TYPE,'R') FROM RPS.VAPC_DETAIL VAPC_DETAIL LEFT OUTER JOIN RPS.TMAIL_SPCLTY_NABP TMAIL_SPCLTY_NABP ON VAPC_DETAIL.NABP_CODE = TMAIL_SPCLTY_NABP.NABP_CODE WHERE VAPC_DETAIL.PERIOD_ID = $$MAX_RPSDM_PERIOD_ID --AND VAPC_DETAIL.RBEL_CLNT_CD = '1' GROUP BY VAPC_DETAIL.PERIOD_ID , VAPC_DETAIL.CNTRL_NO , VAPC_DETAIL.CLM_USE_SRX_CD , VAPC_DETAIL.INV_MODEL , VAPC_DETAIL.RBATE_ID , COALESCE(VAPC_DETAIL.RBEL_CLNT_CD,' ') , VAPC_DETAIL.MAR_CD , VAPC_DETAIL.EXTNL_SRC_CODE , VAPC_DETAIL.EXTNL_LVL_ID1 , COALESCE(TMAIL_SPCLTY_NABP.PHMCY_DSPNS_TYPE,'R') , VAPC_DETAIL.LCM_CODE , VAPC_DETAIL.NDC

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: 7/27/09 - This is a dummy session to update the TAPC_QTR_PRCS table. It will update the start and end time of the workflow. The update is done in a PRE SQL on the Target. The target connection is GDX. For errors, the Source connection is changed to an Oracle database in order to fail. The reason to fail is to be able to update the status. The previous session has to have the box to fail parent tasked UNCHECKED.

SESSION.DESCRIPTION: This session can be used to get date ranges for certain period types. It uses the VRAP.VRCIT_MODEL_PRD_STUS view, and you pass in the CLM_LOCK_CD and APC_STAT_CD values. It puts out the MIN/MAX Quarter period and Monthly periods, along with their associated Start and End dates, based on what values you pass in. Since it builds a Parameter file for use in another session, you also need to pass in the Folder, Workflow, and the Worklet or Session that will be using the new Parameter file.
SESSION.NAME: s_m_Get_Period_Dt_Ranges
